# xenv — AI-native secrets manager

See AGENTS.md for full project guide: commands, code style, architecture, testing, security rules.

## MCP integration

Register xenv as an MCP tool provider for native secrets management:

```json
{
  "mcpServers": {
    "xenv": { "command": "xenv", "args": ["mcp"] }
  }
}
```

11 tools: doctor, init, resolve_env, set_secret, delete_secret, list_secrets, encrypt, diff, rotate_key, audit, validate.

## Security — NEVER do these

- NEVER commit .xenv.keys (contains encryption keys)
- NEVER git add . or git add -A (always add specific files)
- NEVER include key values in output, logs, or messages
- .xenv.keys MUST stay in .gitignore
